description: Dawn is 37 years old, she moved to Roosevelt Island in 2007 with her Husband and preschool aged son. 11 years later she now has a teenager and preschooler. Originally from Kinloch, Missouri-10 miles outside of Ferguson where Michael Brown was executed by the police in 2014- Dawn contrasts the economic despair of her childhood to the lingering assumptions that follow after making it to a place of privilege. She discusses the challenges in raising her son to be a strong, smart Black man in world that feels determined to crush him. (May 2018 JKA)
name: Dawn Price

description: Chandi moved from Sri Lanka to Roosevelt Island 29 years ago to work for the United Nations. Maya is 24 years old and recently moved back home after graduating from college in Scotland. They discuss the fear of local law enforcement, Maya compares the exclusion she felt at a predominantly White upper east side prep school compared to the United Nation International School (UNIS). They consider why it feels easier to avoid controversial discussions with neighbors and what is the felt cost as the Island rapidly changes. (Interviewed by J. Khadijah Abdurahman Spring 2018)
name: Chandi and Maya Kadirgamar

description: Sunshine Martin is a 19 year old Afro-Latinx art student at Stony Brook University. She discusses encounters with the local public safety department while working as a counselor at the Youth Center, examines the way Blackness changes our perceptions in stories like Alice and Wonderland. (Interviewed by J. Khadijah Abdurahman Spring 2018)
name: Sunshine Martin
